class modeling.modeling.WarmupLR(optimizer: Optimizer, warmup_steps: int | float = 25000, last_step: int = -1)[source]

Bases: _LRScheduler

The WarmupLR scheduler

This scheduler is almost same as NoamLR Scheduler except for following difference:

NoamLR:
lr = optimizer.lr * model_size ** -0.5

  • min(step ** -0.5, step * warmup_step ** -1.5)

WarmupLR:
lr = optimizer.lr * warmup_step ** 0.5

  • min(step ** -0.5, step * warmup_step ** -1.5)

Note that the maximum lr equals to optimizer.lr in this scheduler.

Compute the macro soft F1-score as a cost. Average (1 - soft-F1) across all labels. Use probability values instead of binary predictions.

Returns:

cost (scalar Tensor): value of the cost function for the batch

class modeling.utilities.TrainerCallback[source]

Bases: Callback

Callback for modules that train other modules.

If the trained LightningModule has a trains attribute, the callback will save the trained modules in the log directory.

Called when saving a checkpoint to give you a chance to store anything else you might want to save.

Args:

trainer: the current Trainer instance. pl_module: the current LightningModule instance. checkpoint: the checkpoint dictionary that will be saved.
